Nix build patch: drop `prettier` from `opencode generate`.

Upstream declares `prettier` only in the workspace-root `package.json`. The
nix build (`nix/node_modules.nix`) uses `bun install --filter '!./' --filter
'./packages/opencode' ...`, which explicitly excludes root deps. As a result
`prettier` never lands in the sandboxed `node_modules`, and `bun build
--single` fails statically resolving the dynamic imports in `generate.ts`.

The `opencode generate` command is only used upstream to format the
committed OpenAPI schema file. Emit raw JSON and skip prettier entirely -
we don't invoke this command locally.

diff -ruN a/packages/opencode/src/cli/cmd/generate.ts b/packages/opencode/src/cli/cmd/generate.ts
--- a/packages/opencode/src/cli/cmd/generate.ts	1969-12-31 19:00:01.000000000 -0500
+++ b/packages/opencode/src/cli/cmd/generate.ts	2026-04-18 00:00:00.000000000 -0500
@@ -27,17 +27,11 @@
     }
     const raw = JSON.stringify(specs, null, 2)
 
-    // Format through prettier so output is byte-identical to committed file
-    // regardless of whether ./script/format.ts runs afterward.
-    const prettier = await import("prettier")
-    const babel = await import("prettier/plugins/babel")
-    const estree = await import("prettier/plugins/estree")
-    const format = prettier.format ?? prettier.default?.format
-    const json = await format(raw, {
-      parser: "json",
-      plugins: [babel.default ?? babel, estree.default ?? estree],
-      printWidth: 120,
-    })
+    // Nix patch (nix-config): prettier is not in the sandboxed node_modules
+    // (declared only at the workspace root, filtered out by
+    // nix/node_modules.nix). `opencode generate` is only used upstream to
+    // format the committed OpenAPI schema, so emit raw JSON instead.
+    const json = raw
 
     // Wait for stdout to finish writing before process.exit() is called
     await new Promise<void>((resolve, reject) => {
